I'm not really sad, but I am kind of. I am mostly just disappointed. In others, in myself, but I guess there isn't anything I can do, anything I can regret, I can only keep pushing forth. I am grateful for the experiences I have, because they teach me more than any lecture, religion or book could ever teach me. I am at a loss of words right now and I don't really know what to do, I suppose I can just take everything in and decide later. (deep sigh). Hopefully when it isn't 2am I'll be able to analyze this situation and my life with a clear state of mind. With a clear vision. I don't want to judge, I really just want to understand. I want to understand why this makes me sad, why it doesn't make others sad, and why I was put into this situation. Did I choose this? Is this fate? It is probably a little of both.

This probably doesn't make sense to most of you reading this. In fact, probably everyone that reads this won't understand, but I'm sure you can relate it to some part of your life, somehow. right?

uhm... damn i dont know!! I thought i wanted to be a lawyer, but as i was reading "law school confidential" i dont think i'm ready and willing to do it. I don't really want to give up a social life for law school. I want to be affluent and make a difference in the world, but i dont want to neccessarily go to law school or get into politics. I definitely do not want to have a meaningless, mediocre career that only impacts people slightly either. I want to make a big change this lifetime. The only thing is that sometimes I give up on the world, sometimes I get the feeling that people don't want to help themselves and that depresses me.
